- The `catch` block (lines 5–6) rethrows an `IOException`, but the TWR cleanup for `ois` has *already occurred* before entering the catch block — so no path bypasses the close.

Hence, only one execution path exists (the entire function body), and it contains exactly one propagation: Sink (implicit close via TWR). All other propagation types are absent.

